{:component/id :orbiplex/sensorium-workbench
 :component/title "Sensorium Workbench"
 :component/type :node-attached-actuator
 :component/status :partial

 :summary
 "High-impact local workbench actuator for bounded terminal sessions,
 workspace file views, managed-copy virtual execution, artifact-backed patch
 application, waits/probes, and metadata-first recovery under Sensorium and
 host policy."

 :must-implement
 [{:cap/id :sensorium-workbench-capability-boundary
   :title "Workbench Capability Boundary"
   :kind :authority-boundary
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/071-sensorium-workbench.md"
              "doc/project/60-solutions/030-sensorium/030-sensorium.md"
              "doc/project/60-solutions/037-capability-registry/037-capability-registry.md"]
   :schemas ["capability-authorization-policy.v1"
             "sensorium-workbench-outcome.v1"]
   :responsibilities
   ["Register terminal file patch and environment Workbench capability ids"
    "Keep Workbench authority separate from Sensorium OS grants"
    "Expose Workbench actions only through Sensorium-mediated connector routing"
    "Preserve the rule that Inquirium proposes intents but cannot invoke connectors directly"
    "Bind effect classes to grants caller posture approval mode autonomy floor and COI policy"]
   :status :done
   :status-detail "Capability ids, policy sidecars, broker grant admission, exact/prefix operator consent, shared sidecar merge, and operator consent inspection/revocation are implemented."}

  {:cap/id :sensorium-workbench-shared-actuation-core
   :title "Shared Actuation Core"
   :kind :safety-core
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/071-sensorium-workbench.md"
              "doc/project/40-proposals/048-sensorium-os-connector-action-classes.md"]
   :schemas ["sensorium-relative-path-address.v1"
             "sensorium-command-profile.v1"
 "sensorium-command-intent.v1"
  "sensorium-workbench-tool-request.v1"
             "sensorium-pty-resource-caps.v1"
             "sensorium-actuation.bridge.request.v1"
             "sensorium-actuation.bridge.response.v1"]
   :responsibilities
   ["Provide reusable path syntax and containment rules"
    "Reject traversal NUL bytes symlink escape invalid root access and root mismatch"
    "Validate command profiles as argv data rather than shell strings"
    "Enforce default-deny workspace roots and variable argv prefix behavior"
    "Publish golden vectors consumed by Rust and Python conformance tests"]
   :status :done
   :status-detail "Shared Rust cores, schemas, examples, and golden vectors exist; Workbench invokes the bounded required Rust companion process and fails closed when it is unavailable or malformed."}

  {:cap/id :sensorium-workbench-local-connector-runtime
   :title "Local Workbench Connector Runtime"
   :kind :connector-runtime
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/071-sensorium-workbench.md"
              "doc/project/60-solutions/016-bounded-local-server-runtime/016-bounded-local-server-runtime.md"
              "doc/project/60-solutions/019-middleware/019-middleware.md"]
   :schemas ["sensorium-workbench-environment.v1"
             "sensorium-terminal-session.v1"
             "sensorium-terminal-command.v1"
             "sensorium-terminal-event.v1"
             "sensorium-terminal-screen-snapshot.v1"
             "sensorium-file-snapshot.v1"
             "sensorium-file-read-result.v1"
             "sensorium-workbench-outcome.v1"]
   :responsibilities
   ["Run as an opt-in supervised middleware connector"
    "Admit only explicitly configured host-local workspace roots"
    "Expose bounded file snapshot and read without ambient filesystem access"
    "Create bounded PTY sessions only when terminal runtime is explicitly enabled"
    "Execute structured command intents without shell interpolation"
    "Keep raw terminal input resize and signal operator-only in the foundation slice"]
   :status :done
   :status-detail "The opt-in connector runtime implements host-local and managed fixture-copy workspaces, PTY/file/patch/artifact operations, replay, recovery, export, teardown, and operator status."}

  {:cap/id :sensorium-workbench-patch-artifact-writes
   :title "Patch and Artifact-Mediated Writes"
   :kind :effect-boundary
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/071-sensorium-workbench.md"
              "doc/project/60-solutions/023-artifact-delivery/023-artifact-delivery.md"]
   :schemas ["sensorium-workbench-patch.v1"
             "sensorium-workbench-patch-apply-result.v1"
             "sensorium-file-read-result.v1"]
   :responsibilities
   ["Require patch apply to consume artifact refs rather than raw model output"
    "Verify artifact digest and size before application"
    "Support structured edits and narrow unified-diff application"
    "Reject deletes by default"
    "Enforce the same workspace containment and symlink rules as reads"
    "Record metadata-only outcomes and rollback partial structured writes when possible"]
   :status :done
   :status-detail "Artifact-backed patch apply exists behind grants and operator confirmation; verified bytes can be handed off explicitly to Artifact Delivery resolution and metadata-only Memarium provenance."}

  {:cap/id :sensorium-workbench-interaction-deferred-coordination
   :title "Interaction and Deferred Coordination"
   :kind :coordination
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/071-sensorium-workbench.md"
              "doc/project/60-solutions/035-interaction-broker/035-interaction-broker.md"
              "doc/project/60-solutions/029-bounded-deferred-operations/029-bounded-deferred-operations.md"]
   :schemas ["interaction-broker-watch.v1"
             "interaction-broker-wait.request.v1"
             "interaction-broker-wait.outcome.v1"
             "interaction-broker-probe.v1"
             "deferred-operation.v1"
             "deferred-operation-status.v1"]
   :responsibilities
   ["Expose short waits and probes for command file artifact environment and no-progress conditions"
    "Implement the Workbench-owned terminal and file source-provider adapter for the broker-owned source registry"
    "Keep cross-source waits watches and probes host-owned through Interaction Broker"
    "Project long waits through deferred-operation-status.v1"
    "Require explicit status-read grants"
    "Prevent wait timeout or maybe_hung diagnostics from authorizing process termination"]
   :status :done
   :status-detail "Connector and host broker waits/probes/watches, durable resources, grants, audit, recovery/retention, Workbench adapters, dynamic providers, and native Artifact Delivery, approval, and Memarium-query providers are implemented."}

  {:cap/id :sensorium-workbench-storage-recovery-status
   :title "Storage, Recovery, and Operator Visibility"
   :kind :temporal-storage
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/071-sensorium-workbench.md"
              "doc/project/60-solutions/028-temporal-storage-convention/028-temporal-storage-convention.md"]
   :schemas ["sensorium-terminal-event.v1"
             "sensorium-workbench-outcome.v1"
             "interaction-broker-wait.outcome.v1"]
   :responsibilities
   ["Keep Workbench and broker stores metadata-first"
    "Avoid storing raw terminal transcripts file contents prompts source blobs or credentials by default"
    "Use migrations WAL busy_timeout foreign keys idempotency keys retention windows and replay diagnostics"
    "Run startup recovery before accepting new local effects"
    "Surface residual children cleanup failures interrupted waits and degraded recovery facts to operator status"]
   :status :done
   :status-detail "Connector and broker metadata stores, cleanup/recovery facts, bounded retention, provider health, recent-resource projection, remediation paths, and node-ui operator views are implemented."}

  {:cap/id :sensorium-workbench-adversarial-conformance
   :title "Adversarial Actuator Conformance"
   :kind :conformance-suite
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/071-sensorium-workbench.md"]
   :schemas ["sensorium-relative-path-address.v1"
             "sensorium-command-profile.v1"
             "sensorium-terminal-command.v1"
             "sensorium-workbench-patch-apply-result.v1"]
   :responsibilities
   ["Maintain refusal-first golden vectors for path command PTY network credential cleanup idempotency replay broker patch and artifact cases"
    "Run vectors against shared Rust cores and Python connector tests"
    "Refuse enabling write or PTY features by default until relevant negative vectors pass"
    "Keep the conformance suite as the cross-language contract"]
   :status :done
   :status-detail "Refusal and integration vectors cover path, command, PTY, patch, artifact, grants, consent, bridge behavior, broker waits, replay, managed-copy export/teardown, and local smoke."}]

 :may-implement
 [{:cap/id :sensorium-workbench-virt-backends
   :title "Sensorium Virt Backends"
   :kind :future-backend
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/071-sensorium-workbench.md"]
   :schemas ["sensorium-operational-context.v1"
             "sensorium-workbench-environment.v1"
             "sensorium-terminal-session.v1"
             "sensorium-virt-workspace-export.v1"
             "sensorium-virt-export-result.v1"
             "sensorium-virt-teardown-result.v1"
             "sensorium-virt-backend-capabilities.v1"
             "sensorium-virt-environment-plan.v1"
             "sensorium-virt-image-manifest.v1"
             "sensorium-virt-recovery-record.v1"
             "sensorium-virt-guest-frame.v1"]
   :responsibilities
   ["Interpret the same environment terminal file artifact and teardown contracts over virtualized backends"
    "Match normalized environment requirements against host-attested locality isolation fidelity transport device network host-share lifecycle and resource properties"
    "Use closed versioned semantic capability vocabularies and refuse unknown backend or platform refs"
    "Bind effective P082 operational context policy floors and attached-resource context into the normalized plan"
    "Prove logical image equivalence from common userspace SBOM provenance guest-agent and protocol schema-set digests"
    "Separate EnvironmentBackend lifecycle mechanics from the bounded GuestWorkbenchChannel protocol"
    "Keep capability and plan validation plus VMM launch recovery and teardown authority in Rust and the daemon-owned host broker"
    "Use vfkit-system.v1 on macos-vz-arm64.v1 as the first implementation slice and Cloud Hypervisor as the first Linux deployment profile"
    "Require a nonce and generation bound virtio-vsock guest agent without SSH IP host shares or ambient credentials"
    "Treat diagnostic serial as bounded classified untrusted bytes and sanitize operator presentation"
    "Preserve Workbench contracts across backend changes"]
   :status :partial
   :status-detail "fixture-copy.v1 implements bounded managed-copy allocation, patch, export, lifecycle projection, and teardown while refusing PTY. The property-based backend model, closed capability vocabularies, plan-bound operational context and floors, evidence-based logical image equivalence, sanitized diagnostic serial, vfkit-first reference sequence, separate VMM and guest ports, no-snapshot recovery posture, and conformance gate are frozen; the new capability/plan/image/recovery/guest-frame contracts, host broker, guest agent, vfkit runtime/evidence, and later Linux backends remain unimplemented."}

  {:cap/id :sensorium-workbench-agent-corpus-tool-use
   :title "Agent Corpus and Room Tool Use"
   :kind :integration
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/071-sensorium-workbench.md"
              "doc/project/40-proposals/073-agent-orchestration-organ.md"
